trans-unit.source: Represents date and time data ranging in value from January 1, 4712 BC to December 31, 4712 AD.
To obtain an <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDateTime> object, call the <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDataReader.GetOracleDateTime%2A> method.
The minimum valid date for an <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDateTime> structure is 1/1/0001 00:00:00.
However, Oracle supports dates as early as January 1, 4712 BC.
To bind BC dates, use a `String` parameter and the Oracle TO_DATE or TO_CHAR conversion functions for input and output parameters respectively.
